
Overview of noun disintegration

The noun disintegration has 5 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                 
1. (2) decomposition, disintegration -- (in a decomposed state)
2. disintegration -- (a loss (or serious disruption) of organization in some system; "a disintegration of personality")
3. dissolution, disintegration -- (separation into component parts)
4. decay, radioactive decay, disintegration -- (the spontaneous disintegration of a radioactive substance along with the emission of ionizing radiation)
5. annihilation, disintegration -- (total destruction; "bomb tests resulted in the annihilation of the atoll")
